:: \ Platform 7B - Second Time Cont. {"position":"475,1925","size":"100,100"}
<div class="scene">
  <img src="https://i.pinimg.com/736x/06/c0/25/06c025fe03e0300397ffa7297a41d5f8.jpg">
  <div class="text">
    Same angle. Same fold in the page.
    
    The businessman checks his watch. You count. Three seconds. He does it again.
    
    Exact same gesture. Exact same timing.
    
    The teenager bobs their head. One-two-three-four. One-two-three-four.
    
    Same rhythm. Like a loop.
    
    The PA crackles: "The 7:15 service to Millbank will arrive in two minutes. Please stand behind the yellow line."
    
    Same voice. Same inflection. Same static pop at the end.
    
    Everything identical.
    
    Not similar. Identical.

    [[Talk to someone->Breaking the Pattern]]
    [[Search for differences->Scanning for Differences]]
    [[Board the train->Boarding - Second Loop No Ticket]]
  </div>
</div>


:: Arrival at Millbank {"position":"525,900","size":"100,100"}
<div class="scene">
  <img src="https://preview.redd.it/pximnodv3in21.png?width=1080&crop=smart&auto=webp&s=178e3f80d263a3ccd86c52f44949ea45e9636174">
  <div class="text">
    "Now arriving at Millbank Station. Millbank Station. Please mind the gap between the train and the platform."
    
    The doors open. You step onto familiar ground.
    
    Escalators ahead. Coffee shop to the left, same burnt-bean smell. The busker by the exit, violin case open, playing that mournful piece he always plays.
    
    You climb the stairs to street level. 
    
    The office building rises ahead. Glass and steel. Fluorescent purpose.
    
    Your phone buzzes.
    
    Same email. "URGENT: Q3 Reports Due EOD"
    
    Sent: Tomorrow, 6:47 AM
    
    Wait. Didn't you already—?
    
    Déjà vu. Has to be.
    
    You head toward the building.
    
    [[Enter->Reset]]
  </div>
</div>


:: Boarding - Second Loop {"position":"325,2350","size":"100,100"}
<div class="scene">
  <img src="https://i.pinimg.com/1200x/cd/7d/71/cd7d71709ffdac99656ec3a4339ead9e.jpg">
  <div class="text">
    The doors hiss open. You step inside quickly, hand wrapped around the ticket in your pocket.
    
    Same seat. Middle of the carriage. Blue and gray fabric.
    
    You sit down.
    
    Something's wrong.
    
    The other passengers—they're not moving.
    
    At all.
    
    The businessman frozen mid-reach for his briefcase. The woman's hand suspended above her newspaper, caught mid-page-turn.
    
    Not breathing. Not blinking.
    
    Mannequins.
    
    Then—movement.
    
    Footsteps.
    
    Heavy. Deliberate. Wrong.
    
    From the far end of the carriage, a figure approaches.
    
    A conductor. But not the one from before.
    
    His uniform is wrong—too dark, almost black, like it's absorbing light. His face is pale. Waxy. No expression at all.
    
    He doesn't blink. Just walks. One foot. Then the other. Eyes locked on you.
    
    You try to look away.
    
    You can't.
    
    He stops directly in front of you.
    
    "Ticket," he says. His voice sounds like static between radio stations.

    [[Show him your regular ticket->Wrong Ticket]]
    [[Show him the strange ticket->The Strange Ticket Revealed]]
    [[Say nothing->Silent Refusal]]
  </div>
</div>


