:: Boarding the Train {"position":"525,650","size":"100,100"}
<div class="scene">
  <img src="https://i.pinimg.com/1200x/cd/7d/71/cd7d71709ffdac99656ec3a4339ead9e.jpg">
  <div class="text">
    The doors hiss open. You step inside.
    
    The usual crowd for 7:15—not packed, but no empty rows either. You find a seat in the middle of the carriage. Blue and gray fabric, that pattern designed to hide every stain from the last decade.
    
    The conductor passes through. Tall, thin, uniform pressed sharp. He doesn't check tickets. Never does on Tuesdays.
    
    The platform slides away outside your window. The city dissolves into grey-brown industrial sprawl. Warehouses. Overpasses. Graffiti you've memorized.
    
    Twenty-three minutes to Millbank. Always twenty-three minutes.
    
    [[Close your eyes->Journey Observation]]
  </div>
</div>


:: Breaking the Pattern {"position":"325,2000","size":"100,100"}
<div class="scene">
  <img src="https://i.pinimg.com/736x/06/c0/25/06c025fe03e0300397ffa7297a41d5f8.jpg">
  <div class="text">
    You approach the woman in the red coat.
    
    "Excuse me, can I ask you something?"
    
    She looks up. "Yes?"
    
    "Do you- do you feel like we're stuck? Like this keeps happening?"
    
    Her face twists. Disgust. Confusion.
    
    "Get away from me." She backs up, clutching her newspaper. "Another bloody lunatic."
    
    She hurries toward the far end of the platform.
    
    You stand there, heart sinking. Alone. Completely alone in this.
    
    Then you see it.
    
    On the ground near the yellow line. Something that wasn't there before.
    
    Or was it?
    
    [[What is that? ->The Ticket]]
  </div>
</div>


