:: Denial {"position":"725,1525","size":"100,100"}
<div class="scene">
  <img src="https://i.pinimg.com/736x/6c/53/9a/6c539acb16ee42c1fcc3f58c68401e5d.jpg">
  <div class="text">
    Just a dream. Has to be. Stress from work. Too many late nights, not enough sleep.
    
    You go through the routine on autopilot. Shower. Dress. Bag. Keys.
    
    Your hands shake when you tie your shoes.
    
    You tell yourself it's the coffee you haven't had yet.
    
    [[Head to the station->Platform 7B - Second Time]]
  </div>
</div>


:: Entry Point {"position":"525,150","size":"100,100"}
<div class="scene">
  <img src="https://i.pinimg.com/736x/6c/53/9a/6c539acb16ee42c1fcc3f58c68401e5d.jpg">
  <div class="text">
    6:47 AM. The alarm.
    
    Your hand finds the button before you're fully conscious—muscle memory from a thousand identical mornings.
    
    The ceiling crack still looks like a river delta. You've been meaning to get that fixed.
    
    Your phone vibrates against the nightstand. Once. Twice. The screen lights up with a work email preview.
    
    [[Check it->Phone Check]]
    [[Leave it->Quick Route]]
  </div>
</div>


:: Forcing the Issue {"position":"275,1675","size":"100,100"}
<div class="scene">
  <img src="https://i.pinimg.com/736x/6c/53/9a/6c539acb16ee42c1fcc3f58c68401e5d.jpg">
  <div class="text">
    You rip the alarm from the wall. Yank the plug straight out.
    
    The beeping continues.
    
    It's coming from inside your skull now.
    
    The bedroom //folds.//
    
    Walls bend inward. Ceiling lowers. The crack in the corner splits wider—opening like a mouth.
    
    The smell hits you. Train oil. Electrical fire. Ozone.
    
    //You need to get to the station.//
    
    The thought isn't yours. But it's absolute. Undeniable.
    
    Your body is already moving toward the door.
    
    [[Run->Platform 7B - Second Time]]
  </div>
</div>


:: Investigation Path {"position":"575,1525","size":"100,100"}
<div class="scene">
  <img src="https://i.pinimg.com/736x/6c/53/9a/6c539acb16ee42c1fcc3f58c68401e5d.jpg">
  <div class="text">
    Okay. Think.
    
    Either you're losing your mind, or something impossible is happening. Either way, you need information.
    
    You get ready slowly. Methodically. Paying attention to everything.
    
    The toothpaste tube—same position on the sink. Your clothes—same spot on the chair. The weather outside—identical grey sky.
    
    Everything exactly the same.
    
    You check your phone.
    
    There's a photo in your gallery you don't remember taking.
    
    Blurry. Taken from inside a train. You can see your reflection in the window, and behind it, written on the glass in condensation:
    
    DON'T TAKE THE TRAIN
    
    Your handwriting.
    
    You check the metadata.
    
    Photo taken: Tomorrow, 7:08 AM
    
    [[Go anyway->Platform 7B - Second Time]]
  </div>
</div>


:: Journey Observation {"position":"525,775","size":"100,100"}
<div class="scene">
  <img src="https://i.pinimg.com/1200x/cd/7d/71/cd7d71709ffdac99656ec3a4339ead9e.jpg">
  <div class="text">
    The rhythm of the rails is hypnotic. //Clack-clack. Clack-clack.//
    
    Tunnel ahead. The world goes dark.
    
    The carriage lights flicker—
    
    First flicker: The businessman across from you—his face is gone. Just smooth skin where his eyes should be. Where his mouth should be.
    
    Second flicker: Still nothing. Empty. Blank.
    
    The lights snap back on.
    
    Your heart hammers. You lean forward, staring—
    
    He's normal. Of course he's normal. Reading his phone, completely ordinary.
    
    You slump back in your seat. Rub your eyes.
    
    Need more sleep.
    
    [[Continue->Arrival at Millbank]]
  </div>
</div>


:: New Loop Cont. {"position":"675,3575","size":"100,100"}
<div class="scene">
  <img src="https://i.pinimg.com/1200x/cd/7d/71/cd7d71709ffdac99656ec3a4339ead9e.jpg">
  <div class="text">
    *BEEP BEEP BEEP BEEP*
    
    The train's departure chime.
    
    You're in the seat.
    
    7:03 AM.
    
    Again.
    
    But this time—
    
    No bedroom.
    
    No ceiling crack.
    
    No alarm clock on a nightstand.
    
    Your eyes open to fluorescent lights. Rattling windows. The steady rhythm of rails beneath you.
    
    You're on the train.
    
    You woke up on the train.
    
    [[Continue->The New Loop]]
  </div>
</div>


:: New Loop Cont. 2 {"position":"575,3925","size":"100,100"}
<div class="scene">
  <img src="https://i.pinimg.com/1200x/cd/7d/71/cd7d71709ffdac99656ec3a4339ead9e.jpg">
  <div class="text">
    The intercom crackles to life.
    
    Not the usual announcer.
    
    That voice. Static and wrong.
    
    The conductor.
    
    //"Welcome to your new normal."//
    
    //"The loop has changed. You punched the ticket. You committed."//
    
    //"From this moment forward, you don't wake up in bed anymore."//
    
    //"You wake up here. On the train. At 7:03 AM. Eight minutes into the journey."//
    
    //"Every loop."//
    
    //"Forever."//
    
    A pause. You hear something that might be breathing.
    
    //"Unless you find another way out."//
    
    //"Good luck, passenger."//
    
    //"The 7:15 service to Millbank will arrive in 20 minutes."//
    
    Static. Then silence.
    
    Your legs give out. You sink back into the seat.
    
    Shaking.
    
    The businessman across from you checks his watch.
    
    The woman in the red coat turns a page.
    
    The teenager bobs to music you can't hear.
    
    //Clack-clack. Clack-clack.//
    
    And you understand.
    
    You've made everything worse.
    
    TO BE CONTINUED...
    
    [[Credits->Credits]]
  </div>
</div>


:: Newspaper Detail {"position":"525,525","size":"100,100"}
<div class="scene">
  <img src="https://i.pinimg.com/736x/06/c0/25/06c025fe03e0300397ffa7297a41d5f8.jpg">
  <div class="text">
    You lean in slightly, catching the headlines over her shoulder.
    
    TRANSPORT DELAYS CONTINUE FOR THIRD CONSECUTIVE YEAR
    
    MAYOR PROMISES INFRASTRUCTURE REVIEW
    
    Below that, smaller: "Local Man Reports 'Missing Tuesday' - Psychiatrists Concerned"
    
    The woman notices. She folds the paper against her chest and gives you a look.

    [[Step back->Boarding the Train]]
  </div>
</div>


:: No Ticket cont. {"position":"775,2700","size":"100,100"}
<div class="scene">
  <img src="https://i.pinimg.com/1200x/cd/7d/71/cd7d71709ffdac99656ec3a4339ead9e.jpg">
  <div class="text">
    The lights flicker.
    
    You exhale. Only now realizing you'd been holding your breath.
    
    Something brushes against your foot.
    
    You look down.
    
    On the floor, just inside the yellow safety line painted along the carriage edge—a ticket.
    
    Old. Yellowed. Creased with age.
    
    You know what it is before you even touch it.
    
    You pick it up. Slip it into your pocket.
    
    Behind you, very softly—a sound.
    
    A chuckle.
    
    Footsteps. Coming closer.

    [[Show him the ticket->The Strange Ticket Revealed]]
    [[Say nothing->Silent Refusal]]
  </div>
</div>


:: No ticket cont. {"position":"750,2525","size":"100,100"}
<div class="scene">
  <img src="https://i.pinimg.com/1200x/cd/7d/71/cd7d71709ffdac99656ec3a4339ead9e.jpg">
  <div class="text">
    "Ticket."
    
    His voice sounds like static between radio stations.
    
    You hand him your regular ticket. Your hand trembles.
    
    He stares at it. Long seconds pass.
    
    Then he smiles.
    
    Slow. Wrong. Like his face is remembering how smiles work.
    
    "Good," he says softly.
    
    He folds the ticket. Once. The sound is too loud in the silent carriage.
    
    Twice. The paper creaks.
    
    "Still choosing the marked path."
    
    He slides the ticket into his pocket. Doesn't punch it. Doesn't scan it. Just takes it.
    
    "Don't worry." He leans closer.
    
    The smell hits you—cold metal, dust, something underneath you can't name.
    
    "You'll get another."
    
    He turns. Walks away. His footsteps echo, then fade.
    
    But he never reaches the end of the carriage.
    
    He just... disappears.
    
    [[...->No Ticket cont.]]
  </div>
</div>


:: Patient Waiting {"position":"375,525","size":"100,100"}
<div class="scene">
  <img src="https://i.pinimg.com/736x/06/c0/25/06c025fe03e0300397ffa7297a41d5f8.jpg">
  <div class="text">
    You wait. 
    
    The crowd shuffles. Someone's coffee smells burnt. A phone rings and cuts off mid-tone.
    
    7:15. The train pulls in. Exactly on time.
    
    [[Board->Boarding the Train]]
  </div>
</div>


:: Phone Check {"position":"525,275","size":"100,100"}
<div class="scene">
  <img src="https://i.pinimg.com/736x/6c/53/9a/6c539acb16ee42c1fcc3f58c68401e5d.jpg">
  <div class="text">
    You unlock the phone and scroll through the email. 
    
    The usual corporate panic—subject line in all caps, three exclamation points, someone's quarterly bonus on the line.
    
    Then you notice the timestamp.
    
    Sent: Tomorrow, 6:47 AM.
    
    You blink. Read it again. Still says tomorrow.
    
    Server glitch. Has to be. IT's been a mess lately.
    
    When you lock the phone, your reflection stares back from the black screen. Dark circles. Hollow eyes. 
    
    When was the last time you actually slept through the night?

    [[Head to the station->Platform 7B]]
  </div>
</div>


:: Platform 7B {"position":"525,400","size":"100,100"}
<div class="scene">
  <img src="https://i.pinimg.com/736x/06/c0/25/06c025fe03e0300397ffa7297a41d5f8.jpg">
  <div class="text">
    Platform 7B. The 7:15 to Millbank.
    
    The digital board flickers: 7:15 - MILLBANK - ON TIME
    
    The PA crackles overhead. "The 7:15 service to Millbank will arrive in two minutes. Please stand behind the yellow line."
    
    The usual crowd. Woman in a red coat, newspaper folded to the crossword. Businessman checking his watch for the third time. Teenager with headphones, head bobbing to a beat only they can hear.
    
    Everything normal. Everything the same.
    
    [[Read over her shoulder->Newspaper Detail]]
    [[Check your ticket->Ticket Check]]
    [[Wait->Patient Waiting]]
  </div>
</div>


:: Platform 7B - Second Time {"position":"475,1775","size":"100,100"}
<div class="scene">
  <img src="https://i.pinimg.com/736x/06/c0/25/06c025fe03e0300397ffa7297a41d5f8.jpg">
  <div class="text">
    Platform 7B.
    
    The woman in the red coat. The businessman. The teenager with headphones.
    
    All here. All exactly where they were before.
    
    But this time you're //looking.//
    
    The woman's newspaper: same headline. TRANSPORT DELAYS CONTINUE FOR THIRD CONSECUTIVE YEAR. Same article below it: "Local Man Reports 'Missing Tuesday.'"

[[Everything looks the same-> Platform 7B - Second Time Cont.]]
  </div>
</div>


:: Punching Now {"position":"325,3050","size":"100,100"}
<div class="scene">
  <img src="https://i.pinimg.com/1200x/cd/7d/71/cd7d71709ffdac99656ec3a4339ead9e.jpg">
  <div class="text">
    No. You're not waiting. You need to END this. Now.
    
    You grab the ticket punch. Position it over the strange ticket.
    
    Press down hard.
    
    *CHUNK*
    
    Everything stops.
    
    The train. The sound. Your heartbeat.
    
    The ticket begins to smoke.
    
    Then burn.
    
    Black flames. No heat. Just wrongness. They consume the paper from the punch hole outward.
    
    The ash doesn't fall.
    
    It rises. Swirls around you. Faster. Faster. Tighter.
    
    Until—
    
    *BEEP BEEP BEEP BEEP*
    
    No.
    
    Wait.
    
    That's not your alarm.
    
    That's the train departure chime.
    
    You open your eyes.
    
    Same seat. Middle of the carriage. Blue and gray fabric.
    
    The ticket—gone. Burned to nothing.
    
    But you never left the train.
    
    Never arrived at Millbank.
    
    Never went home. Never went to bed.
    
    The loop has changed.

    [[Look around->The New Loop]]
  </div>
</div>


:: Quick Route {"position":"675,275","size":"100,100"}
<div class="scene">
  <img src="https://i.pinimg.com/736x/6c/53/9a/6c539acb16ee42c1fcc3f58c68401e5d.jpg">
  <div class="text">
    No time for email rabbit holes. 
    
    Shower. Dress. Bag. Keys.
    
    The routine is comforting. Predictable. Safe.

    [[Head to the station->Platform 7B]]
  </div>
</div>


:: Rebellion {"position":"425,1525","size":"100,100"}
<div class="scene">
  <img src="https://i.pinimg.com/736x/6c/53/9a/6c539acb16ee42c1fcc3f58c68401e5d.jpg">
  <div class="text">
    No. You're not doing this.
    
    You stay in bed. Pull the covers over your head. Close your eyes tight.
    
    The alarm keeps beeping. 6:47. 6:47. 6:47.
    
    It doesn't stop.
    
    The beeping gets louder. Sharper. //Angrier.//
    
    The walls darken at the edges of your vision. Shadows creeping inward.
    
    The air feels thick. Wrong.
    
    Something wants you to leave.

    [[Get up->Platform 7B - Second Time]]
    [[Unplug the alarm->Forcing the Issue]]
  </div>
</div>


:: Recognition {"position":"525,1375","size":"100,100"}
<div class="scene">
  <img src="https://i.pinimg.com/736x/6c/53/9a/6c539acb16ee42c1fcc3f58c68401e5d.jpg">
  <div class="text">
    6:47 AM.
    
    Again.
    
    Your heart hammers against your ribs. This isn't—this can't—
    
    You sit up fast. Too fast. The room spins.
    
    Phone. Check the phone.
    
    Same email. Same timestamp: Tomorrow, 6:47 AM.
    
    But you remember. The platform. The train. The faceless man. The elevator going dark.
    
    All of it. Crystal clear.
    
    Impossible.
    
    Yet here you are. Same bed. Same ceiling. Same crack.

    [[Stay home->Rebellion]]
    [[Go to the station->Investigation Path]]
    [[It's just a dream->Denial]]
  </div>
</div>


:: Reset {"position":"525,1025","size":"100,100"}
<div class="scene">
  <div class="text">
    The elevator doors close.
    
    The lights go out.
    
    Darkness. Complete. Absolute.
    
    Your breathing sounds too loud in the confined space.
    
    One second. Two. Three.
    
    The moment stretches. Keeps stretching.
    
    Then—

    [[...->Reset cont.]]
  </div>
</div>


:: Reset cont. {"position":"525,1200","size":"100,100"}
<div class="scene">
  <img src="https://i.pinimg.com/736x/6c/53/9a/6c539acb16ee42c1fcc3f58c68401e5d.jpg">
  <div class="text">
    *BEEP BEEP BEEP BEEP*
    
    6:47 AM.
    
    Your hand moves to silence it. Stops halfway.
    
    The ceiling. The crack that looks like a river delta.
    
    You were just—the elevator—the office—
    
    Your phone buzzes.
    
    Work email. "URGENT: Q3 Reports Due EOD"
    
    No.
    
    You already read this. You already got on the train. You already arrived at—
    
    This isn't possible.
    
    [[What the hell is happening?->Recognition]]
  </div>
</div>


:: Scanning for Differences {"position":"625,2000","size":"100,100"}
<div class="scene">
  <img src="https://i.pinimg.com/736x/06/c0/25/06c025fe03e0300397ffa7297a41d5f8.jpg">
  <div class="text">
    Your eyes sweep the platform. There has to be something. Anything different.
    
    The digital board flickers: 7:15 - MILLBANK - ON TIME
    
    Wait.
    
    You stare at it. The letters shift for a fraction of a second—
    
    7:15 - CANCELLED
    
    Then back: 7:15 - MILLBANK - ON TIME
    
    You blink hard. Did you just—?
    
    Movement catches your eye. You look down.
    
    On the platform ground, near the yellow line. Something that wasn't there a moment ago.
    
    [[What is that?->The Ticket]]
  </div>
</div>


:: Silent Refusal {"position":"525,2525","size":"100,100"}
<div class="scene">
  <img src="https://i.pinimg.com/1200x/cd/7d/71/cd7d71709ffdac99656ec3a4339ead9e.jpg">
  <div class="text">
    You say nothing. Stare straight ahead.
    
    The conductor tilts his head.
    
    Too far. An angle no neck should bend.
    
    "You have something that belongs to the train."
    
    His hand moves toward your pocket. The one with the strange ticket.
    
    You feel his fingers through the fabric.
    
    Ice-cold. Wrong. Like touching a corpse.
    
    You jerk away, breath catching.
    
    He doesn't move. Just stands there. Hand still extended.
    
    Waiting.
    
    [[Give him the ticket->The Strange Ticket Revealed]]
  </div>
</div>


:: Strange Ticket cont. {"position":"425,2875","size":"100,100"}
<div class="scene">
  <img src="https://i.pinimg.com/1200x/cd/7d/71/cd7d71709ffdac99656ec3a4339ead9e.jpg">
  <div class="text">
    You unfold the fragment carefully.
    
    The handwriting changes. Mid-sentence. Mid-word sometimes.
    
    Different hands. Different times.
    
    Some of it is yours. You recognize the slant, the pressure. Some isn't. Some you can't place at all.
    
    You read:
    
    //I don't know if this will help. It's the only thing I could think to leave.//
    
    //This ticket isn't about where the train goes. It's about what happens after.//
    
    //If you leave it alone, the day keeps restarting. You wake up somewhere familiar.//
    
    //If you punch it, the train stops letting go.//
    
    //I thought making a choice would end this. It didn't. It only changed where it starts.//
    
    //Now I wake up here.//
    
    //There's no fixing it once it's done. I tried.//
    
    //If you're reading this, you still have time. Once you don't, it won't give it back.//
    
    //I don't know how to explain it better than this.//
    
    //—Someone who stayed//
    
    Your hands are shaking.
    
    You look at the ticket punch on the armrest. Brass and black. Waiting.
    
    Then at the strange ticket in your other hand.
    
    [[Punch it now->Punching Now]]
    [[Don't. Not yet.->Waiting (Attempting to Escape)]]
  </div>
</div>


:: The Burning {"position":"650,3400","size":"100,100"}
<div class="scene">
  <img src="https://i.pinimg.com/736x/6c/53/9a/6c539acb16ee42c1fcc3f58c68401e5d.jpg">
  <div class="text">
    Your hand moves.
    
    Not your choice. Your body obeys something else.
    
    *CHUNK*
    
    The punch goes through.
    
    The ticket ignites.
    
    Black flames. Soundless. Cold.
    
    The ash rises. Spirals around your bedroom. Faster. Faster.
    
    The walls blur.
    
    You're falling—
    
    No.
    
    Not falling.
    
    Traveling.
    
    Through darkness. Through nothing.
    
    Through the space between loops.
    
    Through time itself.
    
    Until—
    
    [[...->New Loop Cont.]]
  </div>
</div>


:: The New Loop {"position":"575,3750","size":"100,100"}
<div class="scene">
  <img src="https://i.pinimg.com/1200x/cd/7d/71/cd7d71709ffdac99656ec3a4339ead9e.jpg">
  <div class="text">
    You stand. Fast. Too fast. The carriage tilts.
    
    Or maybe you do.
    
    The other passengers ignore you. Moving in their patterns. Reading. Checking phones. Staring at nothing.
    
    You grab your phone.
    
    7:03 AM.
    
    Eight minutes into the journey.
    
    Outside the window—the industrial wasteland. Grey-brown. Familiar.
    
    But something's wrong.
    
    You scan the carriage. Looking for the conductor.
    
    The normal one. The wrong one. Either one.
    
    Gone.
    
    Wait.
    
    The carriage is longer. You're sure of it. More rows. More passengers.
    
    All of them moving in perfect synchronization. Turn the page. Check the watch. Bob the head.
    
    Exact. Mechanical.
    
    You run to the door between carriages.
    
    Locked.
    
    You yank the emergency stop handle.
    
    Nothing. It doesn't even move.
    
    [[...->New Loop Cont. 2]]
  </div>
</div>


:: The Strange Ticket {"position":"475,2225","size":"100,100"}
<div class="scene">
  <img src="https://i.pinimg.com/736x/06/c0/25/06c025fe03e0300397ffa7297a41d5f8.jpg">
  <div class="text">
    You slip the ticket into your pocket. Fast. Like someone might see.
    
    The moment your fingers close around it, you feel it.
    
    Weight. Significance. //Power.//
    
    This ticket matters. You don't know how you know—you just //know.//
    
    The PA crackles to life: "The 7:15 service to Millbank is now arriving. Please stand behind the yellow line."
    
    Metal screams against metal. The train pulls in, brakes shrieking.
    
    The doors align perfectly with where you're standing.
    
    [[Board->Boarding - Second Loop]]
  </div>
</div>


:: The Strange Ticket Revealed {"position":"425,2700","size":"100,100"}
<div class="scene">
  <img src="https://i.pinimg.com/1200x/cd/7d/71/cd7d71709ffdac99656ec3a4339ead9e.jpg">
  <div class="text">
    You pull out the strange ticket. Your hands won't stop shaking.
    
    The conductor's face doesn't change. But something shifts in his eyes.
    
    Recognition.
    
    He reaches into his coat. Pulls something out.
    
    A ticket punch. Old-fashioned. Brass and black, tarnished with age. The kind that makes a specific shaped hole.
    
    He sets it on the armrest beside you.
    
    *Click.*
    
    Then he places something else next to it.
    
    A torn piece of paper. Same yellowed texture as the ticket. The edges are burned black—someone tried to destroy it. Gave up halfway.
    
    His fingers—too long, too pale, joints bending wrong—tap the fragment.
    
    Once.
    
    Twice.
    
    Without a word, he turns. Walks down the carriage.
    
    The door at the far end opens.
    
    He steps through.
    
    Gone.
    
    [[Read the fragment->Strange Ticket cont.]]
  </div>
</div>


:: The Ticket {"position":"475,2075","size":"100,100"}
<div class="scene">
  <img src="https://i.pinimg.com/736x/06/c0/25/06c025fe03e0300397ffa7297a41d5f8.jpg">
  <div class="text">
    A ticket.
    
    Not yours. Different.
    
    You kneel down. Pick it up carefully.
    
    Old. Yellowed at the edges. The paper feels wrong—too thick, too rough. The text is handwritten in faded ink:
    
    SPECIAL TRANSFER
    FROM: [BLANK]
    TO: [BLANK]
    VALID: INDEFINITELY
    PLATFORM: 7B
    PRICE: PAID IN FULL
    
    At the bottom, in fresher ink—//your// handwriting:
    
    "Don't punch the ticket. Whatever you do, DON'T—"
    
    The message cuts off mid-word. Like someone was interrupted.
    
    [[Pick it up->The Strange Ticket]]
  </div>
</div>


:: Ticket Check {"position":"675,525","size":"100,100"}
<div class="scene">
  <img src="https://i.pinimg.com/736x/06/c0/25/06c025fe03e0300397ffa7297a41d5f8.jpg">
  <div class="text">
    You pull out your ticket.
    
    STANDARD SINGLE
    FROM: ASHFORD JUNCTION
    TO: MILLBANK
    VALID: TODAY ONLY
    PLATFORM: 7B
    PRICE: £4.20
    
    Everything in order. Like always.
    
    You don't remember buying this one. But then again, you buy the same ticket every day. They all blur together.
    
    [[Board->Boarding the Train]]
  </div>
</div>


:: Waiting (Attempting to Escape) {"position":"525,3050","size":"100,100"}
<div class="scene">
  <img src="https://i.pinimg.com/1200x/cd/7d/71/cd7d71709ffdac99656ec3a4339ead9e.jpg">
  <div class="text">
    No.
    
    The note is a warning. A real one.
    
    You slip the ticket and punch into your pocket. Carefully. Like they might break.
    
    The train lurches forward.
    
    The frozen passengers suddenly animate—the businessman reaches for his briefcase, the woman turns her page. Moving in their loops again.
    
    The journey continues.
    
    Twenty-three minutes. The tunnel. The lights flickering.
    
    You arrive at Millbank.
    
    This time, you don't go to the office.
    
    You go home. Lock every door. Check them twice. Unplug the alarm. Yank the cord straight from the wall.
    
    You won't take the train tomorrow. You'll call in sick. Stay home. Break the loop that way.
    
    Simple.
    
    You place the ticket and punch on your nightstand. Stare at them for a long moment.
    
    Then you force yourself to sleep.
    
    Hours pass.
    
    Or maybe minutes.
    
    Time feels wrong.
    
    Then—
    
    [[...->Waiting Cont.]]
  </div>
</div>


:: Waiting Cont. {"position":"550,3225","size":"100,100"}
<div class="scene">
  <img src="https://i.pinimg.com/736x/6c/53/9a/6c539acb16ee42c1fcc3f58c68401e5d.jpg">
  <div class="text">
    *BEEP BEEP BEEP BEEP*
    
    6:47 AM.
    
    No.
    
    You didn't set an alarm. You unplugged it. Ripped it from the wall.
    
    But there it is.
    
    Beeping. Screaming at you.
    
    Your nightstand—
    
    The ticket and punch are glowing.
    
    Soft yellow light. Pulsing like a heartbeat.
    
    Then a voice. Quiet. Everywhere and nowhere.
    
    //"You can't escape by hiding."//
    
    //"You can only escape by choosing."//
    
    The ticket lifts from the nightstand.
    
    Floats. Hovers in the air before your face.
    
    The punch is in your hand. You don't remember picking it up.
    
    Your fingers close around the cold brass.
    
    You understand.
    
    There's no way out but through.
    
    [[Punch it->The Burning]]
  </div>
</div>


:: Wrong Ticket {"position":"225,2525","size":"100,100"}
<div class="scene">
  <img src="https://i.pinimg.com/1200x/cd/7d/71/cd7d71709ffdac99656ec3a4339ead9e.jpg">
  <div class="text">
    Your hands fumble in your pocket. Pull out your regular ticket. The one you bought this morning.
    
    STANDARD SINGLE
    FROM: ASHFORD JUNCTION
    TO: MILLBANK
    VALID: TODAY ONLY
    
    You hold it up with shaking fingers.
    
    He stares at it.
    
    Then at you.
    
    Silence. Just the rhythm of the rails beneath you.
    
    "Wrong ticket."
    
    His voice is flat. Dead. Like static between stations.
    
    He knows.
    
    Your other pocket feels hot. The strange ticket burning against your leg like a brand.
    
    He tilts his head slightly. Waiting.
    
    [[Show him the other ticket->The Strange Ticket Revealed]]
  </div>
</div>


:: StoryStylesheet [stylesheet]
@import url('https://fonts.googleapis.com/css2?family=DotGothic16&display=swap');

tw-story, #passages {
  font-family: "DotGothic16", sans-serif !important;
  background-color: #000;
  color: white;
  font-size: 21px;
}

.scene {
  display: flex;
  gap: 25px;
  align-items: flex-start;
}

.scene img {
  width: 400px;
  height: auto;
  flex-shrink: 0;
}

.scene .text {
  flex: 1;
}

@media (max-width: 700px) {
  .scene {
    flex-direction: column;
  }
}